Reasoning: 
1. cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) - The paper discusses the use of technology in self-tracking and its impact on patient-clinician engagement, which falls under the purview of HCI. 
2. cs.CY (Computers and Society) - The paper discusses the impact of self-tracking on the therapeutic process, which has societal implications. 
3. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper discusses the use of computational methods in analyzing self-tracking data. 
4. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper discusses the use of language in defining the data collection protocol and discussing the data. 
5. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - Although less likely, the paper discusses the sharing of self-tracking data, which may have security implications.
